1800580.text: A common round shield, lightweight and practical.

1800581.text: A shield tailored for chevaliers, able to resist frontal lunge attacks.

1800583.text: A shield used by the ancient giants. Its size is beyond human imagination.

1800589.text: A common bronze hammer, easy to wield.

1800590.text: A hammer made in batch by the blacksmith. It wields a certain lethal power.

1800592.text: A hammer commonly used by the warriors of Giants. It is a symbol of strength.

1800597.text: A hammer used by the fallen Valkyrie in the Battle of the Polar Night. It is filled with the spell of dark, conjuring endless calamities.

1800598.text: A short sword that even a child can use for basic protection.

1800600.text: Meticulously forged by artisans, it's exceptionally sharp.

1800602.text: A sword can only be wielded by the valiant.

1800605.text: A sword converging all the power of the Valkyrie Springwind that was once used to seal the Dimension Demon in Lake Tirnanog.

1800609.text: An axe popular among the barbarian warriors. Looks fearsome in hand.

1800612.text: A legendary axe filled with its forger's soul.

1800613.text: An axe that sank into the Elf Lake and absorbed the essence of the Forest of Elves.

1800621.text: A cursed dagger that thirsts for souls.

1800624.text: A dagger enshrined in the Misery Palace. It's used by the Protector of the Underworld and capable of taking the breath of life of all intruders.

1800625.text: A crudely made wooden bow that deals little damage.

1800626.text: A long hunting bow. Essential for any good hunter.

1800627.text: A crossbow that can fire an arrow hitting a target at great distance.

1800628.text: A highly durable bow made of dark wood.

1800634.text: A book with many ruined pages. Slightly difficult to read.

1800635.text: A book with spells for apprentices to learn.

1800636.text: A book popular among Sorcerers that records commonly used spells.

1800637.text: A precious book that records advanced spells.

1800638.text: The book passed down by the sorcerer who claimed to be the most powerful in the world.

1800639.text: A book with detailed records of various forms of conjuring.

1800640.text: The sacred book passed down by generations of the Ithacan prophets in the east.

1800642.text: The book of the supreme code that bestows infinite wisdom and magic upon its owner.

1800644.text: Musicians' favorite harp. Produces simple music.

1800645.text: This harp is often used by bards to play elegant, emotional melodies.

1800646.text: The harp handed down to future generations by a frustrated musician. It seems to speak of its former owner's grief.

1800647.text: The magical instrument used by Forest Fairies to bring happiness.

1800648.text: The instrument used by sirens to seduce crews.

1800649.text: The instrument that praises the war exploits of the Demon soldiers. It is capable of playing the sounds of Devildom.

1800650.text: Enshrined in the Misery Palace, its melody can manipulate the souls of creatures to fall into the abyss of the Underworld.

1800651.text: The artifact held by the Valkyrie, Inanna, It stimulates the potential of creatures to unlock their soul power.

1800652.text: An orb that emits no luster.

1800653.text: An orb used to gather spiritual power during the séance ceremony.

1800654.text: A transparent orb that contains incredible magic.

1800655.text: An ominous orb that sealed a demon.

1800656.text: A miraculous orb. It's believed among its followers to be able to hear the oracles.

1800658.text: The treasure passed down by generations of the ancestral tribes of the Sunfaith World. It reveals the emblem of the sun.

1800659.text: A magical orb with the power of the Auguring Star. It can reveal the future.

1800660.text: It is said to contain the sight of Uluru, the Primeval Dragon, which can lead to a future of infinite possibilities.

1800661.text: An ordinary cup made of glass.

1800662.text: It's normally used to store spiritual power which can be released in combat.

1800663.text: Carefully crafted from amethyst, it resonates with the magic inside the user's body.

1800664.text: A cup with the power to purify evil.

1800665.text: A cup that holds the healing power of Hierophants.

1800666.text: A cup filled with the water from Elf Lake. It is kind of affected by the blessing of the elves.

1800667.text: A cursed cup containing the blood of an evil dragon.

1800722.text: A magical accessory. Said to be worn by the maiden who guards the Sacred Tree.

1801027.text: The source of magic, it has a variety of uses. However, it's mostly often used to strengthen one's own power.

1801028.text: The power that sustains the Witch on her journey. $B$The exhaustion of Stamina will return you to the bottom of Chrono Tower, and Stamina will be recovered after a period of rest. $B$$B$Exploring Dungeons will expend Stamina.

1801034.text: It can be obtained by using Assistance Doll. Used in Friendship Point shop to buy items.

1801037.text: The husk left behind from its powerful soul that drifts away; $B$golden energy clings to its surface perpetually. $B$Obtained by summoning, and dismantling UR and SSR Doll Soul Stones in the Workshop. Used to exchange items in the Shop.

1801101.text: Entrusted by the Older Caterpillar Brother to find his lost brother.

1801102.text: The Younger Caterpillar Brother was found in the Irminsul Woods, but he seems to have already lost all hope.

1801105.text: The treasure buried by the merchant Ökam before he left his hometown, into which he poured his inexhaustible affection for his hometown.

1801107.text: The sturdy wood that Andy needs.

1801124.text: The badge dropped by Elementalist Anemone.

1801128.text: A special gift to the Witch. Merry Christmas!

1801129.text: The food that the little fox and its companions buried under the snowdrift. Enough to support another migration.

1801588.text: A searing flame made by purely burning magic power. It ascends the Dolls and enhances their skills.

1801592.text: Translucent dew that seals primitive brutality. It ascends the Dolls and enhances their skills.

1802147.text: The guarantees for card pools, Mage & Healer, Destroyer & Guardian, Assassin & Compeller, are counted independently.$B$Eg: On January 26th, 10AM - January 29th, 4AM a player failed to get a UR Doll after 40 Summons of Mage & Healer, so there would be 40-time Summons left before reaching the guarantee, while the guarantee counter would be displayed as "1 UR will be summoned within next 40 times" at the bottom left.$B$At 4AM on January 29, when the chance of a newly replaced Doll Summon is increased, the counter will also be displayed as "1 UR will be summoned within next 40 times", continuing the last guarantee, until a UR Doll is summoned.
